  "title": "Unix/Linux System Administrator (Shift Duty)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Administer and support Unix and Linux systems across production and DR environments.</li><li>Perform system upgrades, patching, hardening, and performance tuning.</li><li>Monitor system health, capacity, backups, and security compliance.</li><li>Execute disaster recovery planning, testing, and failover activities.</li><li>Provide L2/L3 incident support and manage problem resolution.</li><li>Support projects, changes, and maintain system documentation.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in IT or related field, with 8+ years of Unix/Linux administration experience.</li><li>Strong experience with Solaris and Linux production systems.</li><li>Hands-on experience in OS hardening, patching, and enterprise backups.</li><li>Proficient in Unix/Linux scripting for automation.</li><li>Familiarity with SAN, data centre, or cloud environments is an advantage.</li><li>Able to support 24/7 rostered operations and after-hours changes.</li></ul>",
